post: {'type': 'con', 'text': 'Sensible legal drug policy would uses taxes to keep prices equal or slightly below current black market prices to keep that from occuring. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many users currently do not properly dispose of their paraphernalia for fear of being caught with it on them, leading to evidence of illegal drug use being disposed of quickly and carelessly.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research shows that education has helped the [decrease](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/03/26/cigarette-smoking-decline_n_6855468.html) in number of tobacco smokers. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having drugs be both illegal and valuable has funded extensive infrastructure for smuggling things across the US border.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs are legalised, they will not be as expensive as they are now. Estimations of tax revenue based on current prices may be inaccurate. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During the prohibition of alcoholic beverages between 1920 and 1930 in the US, there were multiple negative impacts on consumers.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If this was true, cartels would already be moving over to newer, patented pharmaceuticals, whose costs of production is dwarfed by market price already.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs are cheap and of good quality, there will be no need for people to buy them on the black market.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During the prohibition of alcoholic beverages between 1920 and 1930 in the US, there were multiple negative impacts on consumers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The drug industry, like alcohol and tobacco, can be heavily taxed, generating high revenues. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's not a given that the low well-being of drug users' families are a result of the drug use. The confounding variable is likely mental health issues. It's possible \\(and sometimes preferable\\) to solve the mental health issues, while not stopping the drug use."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "That's exactly what we have today. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Controlled substances, while controlled, are still obtained through the black market. Whether it is a date-rape drug or marijuana, legislation still cannot control whether illegal drugs are illegally obtained. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Sensible legal drug policy would uses taxes to keep prices equal or slightly below current black market prices to keep that from occuring. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is preferable that if people are going to take drugs, the profit of the industry go to the government to use to provide important services rather than to gangs or drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Controlled substances, while controlled, are still obtained through the black market. Whether it is a date-rape drug or marijuana, legislation still cannot control whether illegal drugs are illegally obtained. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap [substitutes](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Desomorphine#Toxicity_of_%22krokodil%22) like krokodil cause severe health problems. If drugs were legal and cheaper, substitutes lose popularity.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The fact that legalising drugs would not "end all crime" does not means that it would not damage criminal organizations. It\'s a step in the right direction to reduce their power.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has been used as a racist policy to mass incarcerate people of color.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As long as the taxes don't surpass the higher costs of the black market businesses, there is no reason to believe that legal drugs would be more expensive. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's entirely possible for the issue to be intolerance and lack of understanding from the family itself. In those cases, the issue is the reaction of the family, and not the drug use or drug users themselves. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is not a matter of being "viewed as" criminals: under a regime of criminalisation, drug users *are* criminals. It is not a matter of "feeling comfortable" seeking help, it\'s that seeking help would no longer carry the threat of actually going to prison. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education on how to be safe with drugs can be seen as an incentive to use them. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalisation will at length normalize drug use, which can lead to excess use as with alcohol \\(drinking games, binge drinking\\) which can be far more dangerous when done with hard drugs.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalisation of cigarettes [did not stop](https://thedebrief.co.uk/news/real-life/1-every-7-british-cigarettes-contraband-counterfeit/) illicit and poor quality cheaper versions. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In many legal frameworks, the use of drugs is not considered a criminal offense. Only production, commerce, ownership and distribution of drugs are typically illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even though illegal drugs may still exist if drugs were legalised, there would be far less of them than when illegal drugs were the only option. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Citizens would not have to worry about potentially losing their career over using a substance for a medical condition. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Selling harmful products is a poor long-term business strategy, as can be seen with tobacco companies. It only works as long as there is uncertainty in their harms. When the harms become apparent, people will take measures to stop using it as well as take measures to stop others from using it.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is little medical discrimination for those who use legal harmful substances such as alcohol or tobacco.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The law regulation of the drug's market will standardize the quality of the products, and their safety, creating incentives for the consumers to prefer to deal in the legal market. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Some people may become psychologically stressed about a friend/relative coming out as gay, or an atheist as well. That doesn't mean the friend/relative did anything wrong. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This does not take into account plants that do not grow well everywhere. For these cases, there is still a reliance on other communities that fall under different legislation to cultivate the plants. This keeps a connection with the international criminal drug trade.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the pursuit of freedom and promotion of liberty are goals of a state, then the laws surrounding drug use are incompatible with freedom and liberty.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of a drug means more education and informing for children in this matter. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Laws should be introduced on an entirely pragmatic basis, not on the basis of moral signaling. If legalising drugs reduces harm, this should be sufficient evidence that it is a good policy. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs relate frequently with [suicide attempts](https://www.encyclopedia.com/education/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/accidents-and-injuries-drugs). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The cost of alcohol was roughly 3 times higher during prohibition than compared to previous prices \\([pg. 7](http://www.nber.org/papers/w3675.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use has a negative effect on freedom and, therefore, ought to be contained.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The same applies to already legal alcohol. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are highly addictive; [addiction is defined as a disease](https://www.centeronaddiction.org/what-addiction/addiction-disease) by most medical associations.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help drive down the profits of drug cartels since people could get their drugs from legal reliable sources. Hence it may force the cartels to offer a purer product or less expensive to remain competitive. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Nearly all negative effects of addicts on their families are not fueled by the addiction itself, but the fact that the drug they are addicted to is made illegal by the ban on drugs. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs have a long history of responsible use within their historical context.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
